ut only one of them can save your life.<br><br>2h of duo'ing Seb Disco with Phedre holding down both Gruplinort and Brogg spawns, pulling to Necro room.<br><br>Standing mana regen 1, Flowing Thought from items 15, Mental Clarity 3, Epic Rune 3, (it's down occasionally but for simplicity balance that lost mana with the 19 I get for any tick I was sitting), Improved Familiar 6, KEI 14.  42 mana a tick regen.<br><br>With my pitiful mana pool of 4235 after factoring in KEI raising my int to 255, the direct increase from KEI and my Improved Familiar.<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=49182">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...?num=49182</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>In 2h in Disco I had 54635 mana.<br><br>Maxing myself to the mana pool limit as stated in the thread would have given me 55088 mana to spend, seeing as I had mana left when we left it would have provided no benefit, in theory whoring enough items I gain a less than 1 percent increase over a relatively short period of time.  <br><br>Remove the mana cap and go off Rombus' gear, one of the best equipped Wizards in EQ<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5696">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...l?num=5696</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>And we get 50565 mana to spend and not even all focus effects accounted for, but hey that profile does look good, it just chooses style over function.<br><br>But wait, what about the slaying of the UBER mobs.<br><br>Sunstrike base mana 450, base damage 1615 base cast time 7 seconds.<br><br>Concussion base mana 25, base damage 0, base cast time 2 seconds.<br><br>85 percent of Sunstrikes do an average of 1776 damage, 15 percent do an average of 3553.  Meaning the average Sunstrike clocks in at 2043 damage.<br><br>Mage Focus Earring, Spell Casting Mastery III, Spec : Evo 200 means I spend at most 300 mana on a Sunstrike, impossible to confirm through simple math because of the number of variables, I've cast the spell a lot, that number is reliable.  Concussion drops to 20 mana.<br><br>Mage focus ring and cast time is 6.3 seconds, if you have a Level II spell haste item, Concussion is 1.8 seconds, I don't have one though.<br><br>Additional mana regen from the Sebilis example - 6 from Protection of the Grove/Cabbage, 7 mana regen if a bard plays Chorus of Replenishment half the time bringing regen up to 55.<br><br>Cycle of destruction on many mobs is Sunstrike, 2 Concussion, Sunstrike, Concussion and repeat.  660 mana spent in 24 seconds factoring in refresh and choosing a number for the simplicity of 4 ticks of mana regen - 220 mana.<br><br>Net cost is 440 mana, 4086 damage inflicted.<br><br>With my pitiful mana pool of 4235 I can complete 9 cycles for 36774 damage.  One Rod of Mystical Transvergance eatting my Epic and dealing me 100 damage allows me to complete 11 cycles total for 44946 damage.<br><br>4 minutes and 24 seconds into the fight into the fight I've sustained 170 DPS if the fight goes longer than this I'll need more mana, but the key is I won't be the only person OOM at this point, so although you can say well if you had capped mana or even more mana because cap didn't exist you could do more, but this is only true if most notably the clerics aren't OOM, my DPS tends to drop a lot, to about 64 damage in 4 seconds when an UBER mob quads me twice with my 8th Ring up, once the tanks die which happens shortly after clerics go OOM.<br><br>Although it's possible to equip an entire guild to 4238 mana and the now apparently meaningless beyond unquestionably your best solution to dealing with longer than 4 minute fights is a Mage, whether they have a 3000 or 5000 mana pool, they can easily add 26400 mana to an UBER mob encounter without even counting casting a spell once you engage.  Their partner for this is a Shaman who once they have slowed the mob tend to have some mana free to Torpor casters who don't mind getting snared and slowed to get 1200hp for 200 mana.<br><br>******SHORT ANSWER*******<br><br>Mana pool cap is of little consequence, mana pool is one of the most over valued stats in the game, if I really wanted to do a big Manaburn, I would borrow gear as I did against Gorenaire, no reason to worry about it the other 99.9 percent of the time I'm playing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukanoganv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KanoganV</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://mi.wizards.com/magic/generic/storyline/images/islands_info.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/6/02 11:15:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2493.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.battle.net/war3/images/human/units/animations/archmage.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Posting in General sucks</span><hr size=1> Ack!, lol what you mean those poor unfortunates in uber guilds, lol. I dont see anything unfortunate in that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=263313>Kanogan</a><BR>Arcane Conjurer<BR><BR>And here he is.....<BR><img src=http://www.interplay.com/images/young_wizardt.jpg border="0"><BR>The fury of the Summoner....<BR><BR><a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/bdreadstorm>*Dreadstorm*</a><BR><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxaviarstormburnt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xaviar Stormburnt</A></sp